Sentencas: Perovskite oxide, Gd0.6Sr0.4FeO3-delta (GSF) is combined with different ratio of Co3O4 and evaluated as a potential electrode material for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Enhanced performance of Gd0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ electrode by Co3O4 incorporation for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The prepared GSF perovskite exhibits a robust redox reversible stability and shows a remarkable polarization behavior with 30 wt% Co3O4.
Titulo: Enhanced performance of Gd0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ electrode by Co3O4 incorporation for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Furthermore, the single cell performance results show that with the combination of Co3O4, the maximum power density of yttria stabilized zirconia (YSZ)-supported SSOFC enlarges from 244.6 mW cm(-2) to 301.8 mW cm(-2) and the related polarization resistance reduces from 0.62 Omega cm(2) to 0.49 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C using humidified hydrogen (3%H2O) as fuel and air as an oxidant.
Titulo: Enhanced performance of Gd0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ electrode by Co3O4 incorporation for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, the robust 100 h long-term stability test indicates that GSF-Co3O4 composite material is a prospective symmetrical electrode for SSOFC.
Titulo: Enhanced performance of Gd0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ electrode by Co3O4 incorporation for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells
